info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 14 at 4:28AM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Wisconsin River below Alexander Reservoir affecting Lincoln County. Prairie River near Merrill affecting Lincoln County. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM EARLY THIS MORNING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Wisconsin River below Alexander Reservoir. * WHEN...From early this morning until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 1259.0 feet, Widespread wooded lowland flooding downstream of the dam. The river current downstream of the dam in Council Grounds Park is fast. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 4:10 AM CDT Thursday the stage was 1259.0 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 1259.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Please report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and request they pass this information to the National Weather Service when you can do so safely. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued later this morning.
